# Routing Structure

This project uses Next.js App Router with a structured route organization:

## Route Groups

- [src/app/(root)](mdc:src/app/(root)): Main application routes
  - [@dashboard](mdc:src/app/(root)/@dashboard): Dashboard views
    - [@fundAdmin](mdc:src/app/(root)/@dashboard/@fundAdmin): Fund administration
    - [@main](mdc:src/app/(root)/@dashboard/@main): Main dashboard
    - [@portfolioManager](mdc:src/app/(root)/@dashboard/@portfolioManager): Portfolio management
  - [@login](mdc:src/app/(root)/@login): Authentication routes

## Parallel Routes

The project uses Next.js parallel routes (@ prefix) for complex layouts with multiple slots.

## Layouts

- [src/app/layout.tsx](mdc:src/app/layout.tsx): Root layout with providers
- [src/app/(root)/layout.tsx](mdc:src/app/(root)/layout.tsx): Main application layout

## Navigation

Navigation is primarily handled through:
- [AppSidebar](mdc:src/components/app-sidebar.tsx): Main navigation sidebar
- Next.js Link component for client-side navigation
